race.comment: Big field and a host of win chances. TASSORTING (6) has started twice for two minors, the latest trying to lead throughout over 1103m at here. Drawn well and should give a sight again. GRAYNITA (9) started big odds at debit and fought on well for fourth. Has upside and a low draw here. Expected to run well again. RUMBLE TOWN (4) returns from a break and although may want further in time looks nicely placed here fresh. Has been tested in open class and stakes grade already but resumes back in easier company and should be running on hard. ANGEL IN BLACK (7) was strongly fancied on debut and also finished fourth, stalking the lead on the inside and boxing on well. Drawn out this time but looks to have ability and worth including.
